data.title: Jordan Guest
data.text:
Bio

2019-20: Verbally committed to the College of Charleston on April 7...transfer from Boston University...played in 32 games and averaged 8.6 points and 5.5 rebounds...Second-team All-Panhandle Conference...made his Tallahassee debut vs. Enterprise State (11/8/19) and scored 10 points on 4-of-5 shooting...had his first double-digit rebound game with 11 vs. Andrew (11/11/19)...18 points vs. Coastal Alabama-North (11/14/19)...12 points vs. Albany Tech (11/20/19)...pulled down 11 rebounds vs. Odessa (11/27/19)...recorded his first double-double with 20 points and 11 rebounds vs. Coastal Alabama-North (12/3/19)...11 rebounds vs. Albany Tech (12/12/19)...scored in double-figures in five straight games, including 17 vs. Monroe (12/28/19)...13 points vs. Northwest Florida State (1/11/20)...hit 7-of-9 shots and scored 17 points vs. Pensacola State (2/19/20)...18 points on 7-of-9 shooting vs. Gulf Coast State (2/22/20)...10 points vs. Gulf Coast State (3/7/20)...Dean's List student during Fall 2019 semester.

2018-19 (at Boston U): Appeared in 21 games, making three starts...averaged 5.2 ppg, 3.5 rpg and 14.6 mpg while shooting 42.6 FG%...tallied a season-high 15 points with seven rebounds in just 19 minutes of action against Emerson...six points and three rebounds in his debut vs. Northeastern...led BU in rebounds for the first time with six boards at Albany...hit two 3FGs vs. UMass Lowell en route to eight points while adding his first-career steal...named Patriot League Rookie of the Week after posting nine points in a season-high 22 minutes in his first career start against Nicholls State...also recorded four points and three rebounds at Dartmouth...tallied six points and six rebounds vs. Army...posted team-high six rebounds with nine points to help the Terriers snap Colgate's 12-game home win streak during the regular season...dished out a season-high two assists vs. American...signed with Boston over offers from Denver, Utah State, Hawaii, San Francisco, UC Davis, American, Lehigh, Vermont and Hartford.

High School: A four-year letterman at Santa Margarita High School...played for coach Jeff Reinert...averaged 13.4 ppg, 7.6 rpg, 2.3 apg and 0.9 bpg his senior season while shooting 49.2 FG% and 78.3 FT% to help lead team to the CIF State Tournament...finished with 1,250 career points and 782 rebounds while setting the school record for most games played...earned All-Trinity League First-Team and All-Orange County Second-Team honors his senior year.

Personal: Born March 4...son of Nita and Jack Housenga...has one older brother, Freddie...played club ball with Pump N' Run for coach David Rebibo...plans to major in accounting.

Getting to Know Jordan Guest

Favorite TV show: How I Met Your Mother...Favorite movie: Wreck It Ralph...Favorite food: Almond butter...One food I absolutely will not touch: Avocado...Favorite music genre: Hip-hop...What song or artist I like but rarely admit to liking: Russ...What's the farthest I've ever been from home: Boston...If I could visit any place in the world, where would it be: Australia...What is my spirit animal: Finger monkey...What is the top thing on my Bucket List: Raise children and put them through college...What three words best describe me: Social, honest, respectful...One thing people don't know about me: I am a great writer...Person I admire the most: My mother...What's the best piece of advice I've ever received: You'll never be special unless you start doing something that makes you uncomfortable...To get ready for a game, I like to: Listen to "Blood, Sweat, Tears"...Favorite athlete: Kevin Love...Favorite professional sports team: Los Angeles Lakers...My most memorable moment as an athlete: Winning my first game at Boston University.
